        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Avoid retaining menu refresh state",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Avoid retaining `StatusItemController` and the open menu for the full Codex account-scoped refresh task.\n- Capture the long-lived `UsageStore` and `SettingsStore` for the async refresh, while keeping the controller/menu weak in phase-change callbacks.\n- Add a regression test that releases the status controller while an account-scoped refresh is blocked in flight.\n\n## Proof\n- Rebased onto current `main` at exact head `d95db153`.\n- `swift test --filter StatusMenuCodexSwitcherTests`: 22 tests passed, including the in-flight controller deallocation regression.\n- `make check`: format, lint, parser/package/release guards, and locale checks passed.\n- Full branch autoreview against `origin/main`: clean, confidence 0.86.\n\n## Notes\n- This is intentionally separate from the logging performance PR.\n",
